          • [ - ] Jonty - member since 17-Nov-12

            Well played Pep, the tactics were spot on today. Dropping the full backs into the defence and moving the midfielders out wide totally stopped our threat whatsoever from the full backs. Man City were always going to dominate possession but our set up helped them a lot in creating chances especially after Morata was subbed off, there was nobody to hold the ball coming in from the back and no threat whatsoever when you are relying for goals on counter attack. Moreover, nobody pressed on the ball when Man City were playing from the back which they did ever so well against us,one of the reasons why we did not create much until the last 15 or so minutes. The Chelsea midfield was poor today, no one except for Fabregas(who had a poor game himself) has a good passing range in the midfield and which in turn made it so easy for Man City to control the game for the most part. Should have brought on Michy instead on Willian, and Pedro for Bakayoko later on.
